mentions.tacticalSituation: Only the Liberal Democrats can beat Labour in this area. The Green Party candidate came in fourth in 2005, and in the Norwich North by-election they finished fifth with no track record of winning parliamentary elections.

quotes.text: At the last General Election in our area...when the Green Party Candidate last stood in Norwich South in 2005 he came a rather poor fourth.
quotes.source: Andrew Sinclair - Politics Editor BBC Look East

quotes.text: Even the Green Party know that Norwich South isn't their best bet...our best chance, Brighton Pavilion

images.caption: Graphical representation of votes cast in the previous election showing Labour, Liberal Democrats, Conservatives, and Green Party with respective votes of 15,904, 12,251, 9,567, and 3,101.
